Class CreatePageGroupCommand

All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, ICanPromptForKeyValue, ICommand, com.mobius.cache.IHasObjectThatCanBeCached, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.IHasResults, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.IHoldCommandProcessor, INeedFullLoginCredentials, INeedLoginCredentials, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedLoginCredentialsEx, INeedObjectWithDownloadLimit, INeedObjectWithDownloadStatus, INeedObjectWithOutputRenderFormat, INeedObjectWithOutputStream, INeedObjectWithPageList, INeedObjectWithPresentationStream, INeedObjectWithProfileLocation, INeedObjectWithSession, INeedObjectWithStatusMessage, INeedObjectWithStopFlag, INeedObjectWithTraceThreshold, INeedOutputStream, INeedPresentationStream, INeedPromptForKeyValue
public class CreatePageGroupCommand
extends com.mobius.vdrapi.command.QueryCommandBase
implements INeedLoginCredentials, com.mobius.vdrapi.callbacks.INeedLoginCredentialsEx, INeedFullLoginCredentials, INeedObjectWithSession, INeedObjectWithProfileLocation, INeedOutputStream, INeedObjectWithOutputStream, INeedObjectWithTraceThreshold, INeedObjectWithDownloadLimit, INeedPresentationStream, INeedObjectWithPresentationStream, INeedObjectWithPageList, INeedObjectWithStopFlag, INeedObjectWithStatusMessage, INeedObjectWithDownloadStatus, INeedObjectWithOutputRenderFormat

This command object gathers groups of pages, changes their output format, and writes the results to a stream. It has the following parameters:

  • DOCUMENTSERVER "xxxxxx" - this required parameter specifies the document server to connect to. If the document server needs prompting for a user ID or password, this command makes a callback to the INeedLoginCredentials callback.

    A document server's default trace threshold level (for message logging) is set to ViewDirectSeverityLevel.SL_DISASTER, the minimum tracing level. To change the document server's trace threshold level, implement the interface IHasTraceThreshold, and assign the object to this command via setObjectWithTraceThreshold(IHasTraceThreshold traceThreshold).

  • REPORTID "xxxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the Report ID where the page(s) are located.

  • VERSIONID "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the Version ID where the page(s) are located. When a Version ID isn't specified, the most recent version of the report archive is used.

  • SECTIONID "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the section containing the pages to be extracted. When a range of pages are being downloaded and a Section ID isn't specified, pages are retrieved from the first section of the specified version. Please note that a fully qualified Section ID is required when the PAGES parameter value is set to ALLINSECTION.

  • EXACTSECTIONMATCH - this optional parameter indicates whether or not the section ID of of the pages returned must exactly match the section ID passed into the command. If the value is TRUE then only pages from the specified section ID can be returned to the caller.

    To export a group of pages that belong to a particular Topic Item, obtain and then specify the Topic Item report (REPORTID), Topic Item report version (VERSIONID), fully qualified Topic Item section name (SECTIONID), and the number of pages in the topic.

    For an example of retrieving specific pages from a topic item section, refer to the Navigating the Topic Hierarchy section of the ViewDirect API for Java Overview.

  • PAGES - this can be one of the following values:
    • ALL - place all the pages from all sections in the output stream. Section may not be specified.
    • ALLINSECTION - place all the pages from the specified section in the output stream. Report SectionID required. Not valid for Topic Sections.
    • FROM x y - place pages x to page y from the specified section in the output stream.
      The following example downloads a range of pages from 1 to 5:
      paramVector.add (new ICommand.KeyValuePair (CommandKeyType.Pages,"FROM 1 5"));
  • OUTPUTFORMAT - optional parameter. Refer to RenderFormatType for a list of formats supported. If the OUTPUTFORMAT key is not specified, DEFAULT is the assumed value, and pages are retrieved in their default format. The POLICYID parameter is required for the following output formats:
    • CSV - pages are output as CSV files.
    • SYLK - pages are output as CSV files.
    • XML - pages are output as XML files.
    If the specified format is not supported by the pages being retrieved, an exception is thrown.

    Note: If the format specified is SVG or HTML, and either SCALE parameter or WIDTH and/or HEIGHT parameters are not set, SCALE == 100 will be default.

  • PAGEEXTENSION "xxx" - this optional value determines the extension type assigned to the pages as they are written to the output stream. Specify this parameter only if the value of OUTPUTFORMAT is DEFAULT, TEXT, or HTML.

  • ZIP - this optional parameter determines whether the output stream should be compressed. To enable compression, set ZIP to TRUE, as in the following example:
    paramVector.add (new ICommand.KeyValuePair (CommandKeyType.Zip,"TRUE"));

    Note: Set the ZIP paramater to TRUE if two or more pages are being downloaded, unless the output format is PDF, PS, PCL, or TEXT. Additionally, ZIP is not required when multiple AFP pages are downloaded in AFP format.

  • POLICYID "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the POLICY to use when creating CSV, SYLK, or XML output. The POLICYID value must contain the absolute path for the policy file, for example, C:\PolicyFiles\AC001.PLC.

  • POLICYGROUP "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the POLICYGROUP to use with a POLICYID. Specify this parameter only if the POLICYID key is present. If it is specified as "*", all the groups will be exported (this option can be used only with XML as the OUTPUTFORMAT value). When a POLICYID is present and a POLICYGROUP isn't specified, this command uses the policy filename as the POLICYGROUP value, but excludes the file extension.

    For example, if the POLICYID value is "C:\PolicyFiles\AC001.PLC" and the POLICYGROUP key isn't specified, the CreatePageGroup command uses "AC001" as the POLICYGROUP value.

  • COLUMNHEADER - this optional parameter specifies whether to use column headers when applying a policy. Specify this parameter only if the POLICYID key is present.

  • PRESENTATIONNAME "xxxxx" - this optional parameter specifies the presentation name to use when downloading pages. It can only be used in conjunction with a presentation stream, which is specified using the setPresentationStream method of the command's INeedPresentationStream interface. A presentation stream is a file in XML format that is generated by DocumentDirect's Visual Parser. The presentation information can be used to download page(s) with bookmarks and hyperlinks.

  • WIDTH x - this optional parameter specifies the width of each output page.

  • HEIGHT y - this optional parameter specifies the height of each output page.

  • SCALE x - this optional parameter specifies the scale percentage to be applied to an output page.

    The SCALE parameter takes precedence over the WIDTH and HEIGHT parameters. If SCALE is set, even if the value is 0, the WIDTH and HEIGHT parameters would be ignored.

  • ROTATION x - this optional parameter specifies the angle of rotation to be applied to an output page.

  • COLORDEPTH x - this optional parameter specifies bits per pixel to be used for each output page. Specify this parameter only when the output format requested is an image format such as JPEG, PNG, or TIF.

  • GRAYSCALE - this optional parameter determines whether a page is displayed as a grayscale image. Specify this parameter only when the output format requested is an image format such as JPEG, PNG, or TIF.

  • SUBPAGES - this can be one of the following values:
    • ALL - places all the sub-pages within a page in the output stream.
    • FROM x y - places the sub-pages x to y of the specified page in the output stream.

  • QUALITYFACTOR x - this optional parameter specifies the qualify factor to be used when the output format is JPEG. Its value can range from 1 to 100.

  • PASSES - this optional parameter specifies the number of passes to be applied when the output format is JPEG.

  • DPI - this optional parameter specifies the resolution (dots per inch) of each output page.

  • OUTPUTFORMATDECISIONTABLE - this optional parameter is an object of type com.mobius.vdrapi.OutputFormatDecisionTable OutputFormatDecisionTable, and contains output formatting rules for rendering specific page data types. When present the rules specified by the key-value pairs in this object shall be used to format the output of this command object execution. Please note that the same page formatting rules apply for the rules in the table as noted in the Page Format Options table see Page Format Options table. Certain invalid combinations may result in exceptions. Also note that the CreatePageGroupCommand does not perform validation on the output format rules that reside in the table.

The CreatePageGroupCommand can implement either the INeedLoginCredentials or the INeedFullLoginCredentials interfaces. However, if both these interfaces are implemented, the command throws a MultipleCallbacksSetException. Additionally, if the caller implements the IHoldSession interface, then neither IHasLoginCredentials nor IHasFullLoginCredentials is required.

The caller of the CreatePageGroupCommand object must set either setOutputStream( OutputStream ) or setObjectWithOutputStream( IHoldOutputStream ). If multiple download commands are being played back from a script file, the caller should use setObjectWithOutputStream( IHoldOutputStream ), as defined in the INeedObjectWithOutputStream interface.

Similarly the caller of this object must set either setPresentationStream( ByteArrayInputStream ) or setObjectWithPresentationStream( IHoldPresentationStream ). If multiple download commands are being played back from a script file, the caller should use setObjectWithPresentationStream( IHoldPresentationStream ) as defined in the INeedObjectWithPresentationStream interface.

The caller of this object can optionally specify an alternate set of page data conversion rules for translating the downloaded pages by passing in a OutputFormatDecisionTable. A caller would do this if the default conversion rules are not desired.

The caller of this object can optionally request the collection of specific information about the pages being retrieved. When this request is activated, the caller and related "HasA..." and "IsA..." caller objects can access the page list, which is a list of header information about each page retrieved. Because the CreatePageGroupCommand often retrieves pages from multiple sections, the page list can help the caller determine from which section a page or pages were downloaded.

To use this feature, the caller of CreatePageGroupCommand calls setObjectWithPageList. This informs the CreatePageGroupCommand object to initialize and populate a list of type IPageList. The caller is required to manage the tasks of obtaining and setting the page list, using methods implemented for the IHoldPageList interface.
